  sodium: 1320 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-heat-turkey-cauli-bowls-64ef6de2b6b5b459c56f583a
course: main course
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; slice into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Cut @cauliflower florets{10%ounce} into bite-size pieces. Trim @scallions{2}; mince whites and slice greens on a diagonal into ½-inch pieces. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine cucumber, @rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @sugar{¼%teaspoon} (½ tsp for 4 servings), and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Set aside to pickle.

Open package of @ground turkey{10%ounce} and drain off any excess liquid. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{6%teaspoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add turkey and season with salt and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring frequently, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Toss cauliflower on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant and softened, ~{1%minute}.

Add @jasmine rice{½%cup}, ¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a medium pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion greens; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%ounce}; cook, stirring occasionally, until scallions are slightly charred and veggies are tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan.

> Use pan used for chicken or turkey here.

In a second small bowl, whisk together half the @cornstarch{1%tablespoon} and ¼ cup cold water (all the cornstarch and ½ cup cold water for 4 servings) until no lumps remain. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium heat. Add ginger and garlic; cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @apricot jam{1%unit}, @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, cornstarch mixture, and as much @sriracha{1%teaspoon} as you like. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and syrupy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Reduce heat to low.

> TIP: Add water a splash at a time if sauce seems too thick.

When cauliflower is done roasting, add to pan with sauce; stir until thoroughly coated.

> Stir chicken or turkey into sauce along with cauliflower.

Stir cabbage mixture into pot with rice.

Divide rice between shallow #bowls{}. Top with saucy cauliflower and pickled cucumber (draining first). Serve.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.